			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2581')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=39669&amp;TOPIC_ID=4977&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Decent+high+50s+xp&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Sorry about how vague I was, for some reason I guess I just assumed everyone would know where the pits below Vox are. I'm not the best at giving directions so I will refer you to an eqmaps.com map for assistance <a href="http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/permafrost4.jpg" target="_blank">http://www.eqmaps.com/m3/permafrost4.jpg</a> that's the best map I could find. You have to run through Perma, into the Ice Goblin fort, when you enter the first chamber of the IG fort take the first passage leading right, then at next intersection go right, then path will turn down to the right just follow it straight and you should fall through the pit trap into the bear pits.</P><P>There is three seperate pit traps inside the IG fort that you can fall into... and honestly I can't remember which one is the "best" to go down in because it's been so long since I"ve done this. There are a *pile* of giant polar bears and giant wolves down here, most of them are dark blue at 60 from what I hear (was never here later than 59 myself). They have I think 6-7k hp and do hit fairly hard so don't mess up =D. There are a lot of them down there so if you aren't about 57 or 58 you will probably get a lot of adds. No, the bears themselves don't see through invis but some of the giants you have to run past might. If you have run3 you can probably just jet past the giants drop into the pits and camp out as I don't think they follow you down. Pre-Nerf circlet would be best in case one of the giants hits you , you can safely recast it before you have to jump down. You jump down without invis you will probably die and fast. </P><P>You might want to bring a friend along or something the first time you try these, I went down with a guild group a long time ago and that's how I found out about it. Basic kill strategy is simple root cooking, I wouldn't summon a pet up or even try to fear kite them. </P><P>Sorry I can't give the best advice here it's probably been over a year since I"ve been down there but it is decent xp and I know a few necros on my server that went through all of 59 in the pits and did so fairly fast.</P><P>Only loot is meat from the bear and wolves and giant polar bear skins and giant dire wolf skins I believe.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

